 A user-friendly tool for creating bootable media for ZimaOS devices.

Package: zimaos-usb-creator-embedded
Build-Profiles: <embedded>
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, 
         dosfstools, fdisk, fuse, libfuse2, util-linux (>= 2.37), libdrm2,
         libinput10, libudev1, openssl
Suggests: rpi-eeprom, firmware-brcm80211
Conflicts: zimaos-usb-creator
Description: ZimaOS USB Creator for embedded systems
 A user-friendly tool for creating bootable media for ZimaOS devices,
 optimized for embedded systems.
 .
 This version is specifically designed for embedded systems:
  - Uses linuxfb for direct rendering (no desktop environment required)
  - Optimized for network-based installation
  - Smaller memory footprint for embedded applications
  - Supports DRM/KMS rendering

Package: zimaos-usb-creator-cli
Build-Profiles: <cli>
Architecture: amd64 arm64 armhf
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, 
         dosfstools, fdisk, fuse, libfuse2, util-linux (>= 2.37)
Conflicts: zimaos-usb-creator, zimaos-usb-creator-embedded
Description: ZimaOS USB Creator (command-line only)
 A command-line tool for creating bootable media for ZimaOS devices.
 .
 This version is optimized for command-line operation:
  - No GUI components - CLI mode only
  - Minimal dependencies (Qt Core only)
  - Perfect for headless servers, automation and ZimaOS Lite
  - Smaller package size and memory footprint
  - Most imaging functionality available via command line
  - Ideal for scripting and CI/CD pipelines

